This paper deals with the measurement of scientific impact in the digital era, which is a topic that is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science. The paper specifically mentions the use of social network analysis and usage log data, which are techniques commonly used in the fields of digital libraries (cs.DL), social computing (cs.SI), information retrieval (cs.IR), cybersecurity (cs.CY), and software engineering (cs.SD). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
